HEADWORD: Obstipation
<hw>Ob`sti*pa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obstipatio</ets> a close pressure; <ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>)
+ <ets>stipare</ets> to press.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
stopping up, as a passage.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Extreme constipation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Hooper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obstreperous</ent>⟦br⟧
